â€œBless me Father, for I have sinned.  I purchased a 1/2 oz. of Cookies Kush, however my dispensary call it, Golden Cookies, but no matter the regional nomenclature, this batch of Cookies SC Lab tested in at 30.28% THC.

â€œThis was some pretty strong stuff. A few puffs from my vaporizer and I was glued to the couch, virtually unable to budge for hours. After about two hours, it completely knocked me out and I woke up as the movie I had just started was ending. For as strong as the high was, it didn't mess with my brain too much and I was mostly just relaxed as I tried to watch movies with my wife.

There are two reasons that I don't gi...â€
â€œI can't tell you this is a strong weed, cause that is an understatement. It had me nearly unable to carry on a conversation and/or move for about 4 hours. so yeah....â€

â€œTried this strain at Barney's Coffeeshop in Amsterdam and real talk, it was quit a treat. Cookies Cush resembles aromas found in Girl Scout Cookies. Although listed as an indica the effects touch close to a sativa dominate strain. Truly one of the better strains I tried.â€
â€œBeautiful, delish, potent Indica. GrandDaddy Purple still takes the cake as my fave indica but Cookies Kush is a close second. Relaxing,  mellow, zero anxiety, some creativeness, top 10 faves.â€

â€œI've been smoking on some cookies kush for a little over a month now and it's the perfect strain to smoke before bed ğŸ˜ I've been smoking for awhile, but take like 4 bong rips of this and it knocks me on my ass. Really, really, really strong indica hybrid, it's an amazing physical & head high. Great strain to smoke socially, everyone gets super baked super quick. 5/5 stars, will be picking up again!â¤ï¸â€

â€œNote: Review for OG Cookies. Very relaxing body high followed by gradually intensifying cerebral effects. Great for pain management or just lounging around after a hard day's work. Sweet and pungent taste and aroma only lasts the first few hits.â€

â€œBeing born and raised in California, I have a big ol' soft spot for OG Kush. And who doesn't like Cookie strains?? So I had high hopes for this particular strain, as I lovvvvve Indicas especially, and I gotta say, it surpassed my wildest dreams!

Just a single big fat (1.4g) doobie rolled with a king size Juicy Jay Mango flavored rolling paper, and I fell head over heels for this stuff! 

Genuinely impressed by this ...â€

â€œNot what I expected from a cross between GSC and OGK. It is a very nice strain. But when I think GSC or OGK, I think happy, giggly, uplifting, etc. This is very heavy in the face. It certainly has the calming effects. 

Maybe since I experienced this in a dab it was a bit heavy.  It's worth a try. Plenty of worse strains out there.â€

â€œA sweet tasty strain for those who don't like too sacrifice potency for flavour this is you all over. It's sweet but retains that Kush element which gives a strong taste with strong effects. A good evening smoke if suffering from insomnia etc.â€

â€œMethod: Barney's Flower in a Vaporizer

Aroma: It smells, sweet with a bit of spice and fruit. 1/1 Star.
Taste: The sweet takes over at first with a marshmellow-y pastry taste before ending with some berry hints. I think this would be amazing as a vape cartridge to really pull out the right terpenes. 1.5/2 Stars.
Feel: A strong and classic indica. Had to cancel a walking tour I had later that night and just sit on a ...â€
